
- [ ] 2 tsp chilli powder
- [ ] 2 tbsp mixed powder
- [ ] 2 tsp cumin
- [ ] 2 tsp turmeric 
- [ ] 2 tbsp chicken seasoning
- [ ] 2 tsp cajun
- [ ] 2 tsp smoked paprika
- [ ] 2 tsp chilli flakes
- [ ] 2 tsp black pepper
- [ ] 2 tbsp onion powder
- [ ] 2 tbsp garlic powder
- [ ] 2 tsp sumac
- [ ] 2 tbsp mixed herbs
- [ ] 2 tbsp salt
- [ ] 8 chicken breasts or thighs
- [ ] Lemon juice
- [ ] 4 tbsp Nando’s Sauce
- [ ] 3 onions
- [ ] 3 cloves of garlic
- [ ] 2 tbsp tomato purée
- [ ] 1 pot of double cream
- [ ] 150g cheddar cheese
- [ ] 800g conchiglie pasta

1. Boil your pasta 
2. Mix your seasonings, then use half on them to season your chicken breasts then add lemon juice and Nando’s sauce and fry your chicken breasts and then set to one side.
3. Add oil to another pan and then chop three onions and add to the oil, add three cloves of garlic, tomato purée, the rest of your seasonings, then cook these before mixing in your double cream.
4. Mix the pasta into the sauce before plating into 8 servings, slice the chicken breasts into soldiers and lay them on top of your pasta.
